<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no" ?>
<FinalDraft DocumentType="Script" Template="No" Version="2">

  <Content>
    <Paragraph Number="1" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="1" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA">
</CharacterArcBeat>          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Karaoke club - nighT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The year is 1999, two Chicago hotties in their late 20’s enter a karaoke bar full of festive people singing and dancing. As soon as they enter, a strikingly attractive man grabs the hand of one of the women. He pulls her toward him through the thick mass of the crowd. Her friend continues to walk not noticing he is no loner by her side. The woman is fidgety and blushing obviously charmed and lured in by the guy’s seductive eyes and bewitching smile.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She now stands face to face with a stranger hypnotized by his charm. The music is extremely loud making it virtually impossible for them to hold a conversation, but their body language speaks volumes as he drapes his hands around the lower curve of her back, as if they’ve known one another for a life time. She doesn’t resist him. The vibration of the music begins to move their bodies rhythmically together in dance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He takes her by the hand and pulls her to the stage, she resists a little before following him onto the stage. They perform a duet together. Ike and Tina Turners, Proud Mary.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Every now and then we like to do things nice and easy, but you know we never ever do things nice and easy, cause we like to do it nice and rough.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The crowd goes wild. Everyone is dancing and singing along with the couple. Mia’s friend joins her on stage and dances in the background. You can’t hear them singing over the roar of the crowd, but the dance moves speaks volumes. Once they finish singing and exit the stage, they guy pulls a business card out of his pocket and hands it to Mia. The card reads Trevor Wright. As she makes her exit, she turns to get one last look at the man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Trevor</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey. What’s your name?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She is barely able to hear him over the noise of the crowd. He yells out again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I said, what’s your name?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He holds his hand to his ear in a phone like gesture indicating he wants her to call him. She smiles and nods affirmatively.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="2" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="2" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. Mia apartment-bedroom-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is sitting on her bed daydreaming, she looks at the card given to her by the stranger and smiles. She holds the card up to her nose to smell the scent of his cologne. She picks up the phone to dial. She hesitates for a moment and hangs the phone up. She stands and paces around the room. Finally, she takes a closer look at the card noticing an e-mail address. She sits in front of the computer, and logs onto her e-mail account and begins to write.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello Trevor, we met the other night at the karaoke club. I was wondering if you like to get together for a drink later? I really enjoyed you, and would like to get to know you better. ~Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She presses send and puts her hands to her face in a nervous gesture. She then gets up from the computer and begins pacing the floor again. She looks at the screen and notices he responded already. She is really excited and quickly sits in front of the computer to read his reply.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia, I appreciate the invite, but my girl and me are going to a concert tonight. How about a rain check? Take care. ~Trevor</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is heartbroken by a stranger. She can’t believe he came on so strong to her and he as a girlfriend. She is quickly typing her response.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>GIRLFRIEND? SEEMS YOU FAILED TO MENTION THAT THE OTHER NIGHT! WHY WOULD YOU COME ON SO STRONG, AND YOU KNEW YOU HAD A GIRLFRIEND? HOW ABOUT YOU LOSE MY INFORMATION JERK!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Opening credits play over the scene, title reads a FEW YEARS LATER. We see a series of shots of city streets and tall buildings and the flow of Chicago traffic.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="3" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="3" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR GIRLFRIEND"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. karaOKE CLUB-night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A few years have passed. It’s the new millennium. We see an older, but still attractive Mia. She is sporting a hot mini skirt showing off her shapely legs. All eyes are on her when she enters the club. It’s the same karaoke club from years earlier where she first met Trevor, but the crowd is different, no one is singing. The crowd is more laid back. People are </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">texting</Text>
      <Text> on their phones, and not very festive at all. Mia and her friend turn their noses up at the group. A guy is watching her from the distance. He is wearing a baseball cap that is pulled down low, covering a good portion of his eyes. Mia notices the guy looking at her before turning to leave the club. He begins to approach her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>As Mia and her friend walk towards the door, Mia feels a tug at her dangling fingers from behind. She turns to face eye to eye with the guy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Leaving so soon?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, it’s not quite what I was expecting. I remember this use to be a karaoke club.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They still do karaoke on certain nights. It’s not as popular as it used to be.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They continue to walk and talk until they reach the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess that tells you I haven’t been out in a while. You look familiar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia’s friend walked ahead and is already in the car waiting for her while Mia stands outside of the car talking with Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have been told I have one of those familiar faces. Is it okay if I call you sometimes?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Just as Trevor pulls out his phone to store her number, two girls pull up in a car behind him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Trevor Girlfriend</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He turns to look.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh shit...damn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR GIRLFRIEND</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have been calling you all day. What the hell are you doing? I know you’re not getting her number!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor...I thought you looked familiar. You don’t remember me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. Can’t say I do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia knees him in his growing and jumps in the car with her friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Jerk! Does the name Mia ring a bell?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Damn...I</Text>
      <Text> remember you now!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor is doubled over holding his private.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR GIRLFRIEND</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You are such a dog. Let’s go girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby wait. I can explain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="4" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="4" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. trevor apartment-night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello Mia, I hope this is still your e-mail after all these years. I owe you a double apology. I’m not as bad as I can imagine you think I am. I would love a chance to make it up to you. How about dinner on me? It’s an open invitation for whenever you’re hungry. Please accept my sincerest apology pretty lady. ~Trevor</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="5" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. mia APARTMENT-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia opens her e-mail to find a message from Trevor. She smiles as she reads the message and begins to type her response.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Fine. I want to go to the most expensive restaurant in Chicago, Mr. Player.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>SCREEN TITLE READS PRESENT DAY... 2016</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="6" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MIA APARTMENT-KITCHEN-eveNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The stove is loaded with pots and pans, food is cooking. Mia lifts the lid off of a pot of greens; she stirs them and then lifts the lid off of a pot of sweet potatoes. She removes a pan of cornbread from the oven.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia, you got it smelling good in here!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I told you I could throw down Mr. Wright.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’ve been holding out on me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t let you know all of my secrets.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="7" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 3/8" Page="5" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia apartment-dining room-evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor enter the dining room with plates in hand, and they take a seat at the table. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor uncorks a bottle of wine and pours them both a glass. He prepares to take his first bite.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The moment of truth...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He slowly chews. She watches him for a reaction.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mm,Mm,Mm...girl</Text>
      <Text> you’re hurting me, this is delicious!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You had me worried for a minute. I can’t believe as long as we’ve been friends this is your first time tasting any of my cooking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now that I know you can throw down like this, you will be serving a brother up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Music is playing in the background. Mia turns up the volume.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I love this song. Who is your favorite artist?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Prince.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mine too. I was so serious about Prince when I was growing up, that I wanted to play the guitar, just so I could be in his band one day. My Mom actually brought me an electric guitar for Christmas one year.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you serious? I love guitars. Do you still have it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I do. Do you want to see it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia exits the room, Trevor takes a seat in the living room on the sofa. Mia returns with an electric guitar. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wow, this is nice Mia. Does it work?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, it works, but I never learned to play. I wanted a lead guitar and this is a bass. My Mom didn’t know the difference when she brought it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Prince was cold on that lead guitar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I still can’t believe he is gone. I cried so hard when I heard the news; he was my first boyfriend in my head. One of my dear friends who I hadn’t seen in years called me. She said she knew how much I loved Prince, and when she heard the news all she could think of was me. It makes me tear up just thinking about how heart broken I was that day. She invited me for drinks. We laughed and talked about Prince and old times. That meant a lot to me. I will always be grateful to her for that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sound like a good friend. Prince was one of the greats. He was a cool cat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My biggest regret is I never got to meet him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor examines the guitar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know whom else I liked? Old school Ike and Tina. Remember when you and I first met? I talked you into singing Proud Mary with me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. That was so much fun! I really love Tina Turner. She is awesome. I hope to meet her one-day, maybe fly to Switzerland and have girl talk over a cup of tea.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can see you doing that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia has hooked up the guitar. They are playing and having a good time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor phone rings. He answers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Autumn. Ah baby, I’m so sorry. I forgot you were coming by tonight. I’m at one of my friends crib. You remember my girl Mia who I told you about? She cooked us up some killer soul food and we’re just chilling. Look under the mat, that’s where I keep the spare key, be discreet. You got it? OK. Go ahead and let yourself in. I’ll be there shortly. Be ready for me girl!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor hangs up the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh you must really like this one. She has been around for a while now. Trusting her with the key...hmmm?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What can I say? You have been a good influence on me. There’s more to life than being a player.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m glad to hear that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia lets out a deep yawn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re a really good friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You too home biscuit...you too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who would have ever thought that we would become the best of friends?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know you were such a jerk back then.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey, I wouldn’t go that far.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia yawns and nods off in the middle of talking. Trevor gently lifts her head from his shoulder. He rises from the sofa and covers her with the throw blanket. He walks over to the table and cleans it off. After he finishes cleaning off the table, he walks over to Mia and kisses her on the cheek; he grabs his jacket and heads out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="8" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2" Page="9" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BIZ MARKIE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. law office-morning</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A cute young woman in her late 20’s early </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">30’s</Text>
      <Text> is seen sitting behind a desk that contains a computer and phone, surrounded by legal books.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The young lady seated at the desk answers a ringing telephone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Wanda</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Attorney Spencer’s office, this is Wanda, how may I help you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia rushes into the office as Wanda is hanging up the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(whispering)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is the boss here yet?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(sarcastic)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And a good morning to you too, Ms. Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry, good morning Wanda.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes she is, and you my dear are in trouble. She was looking for that file you were working on for the Barry trial tomorrow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh shoot. Are you serious? Can you help me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is seriously stressing. Pacing the floor. Wand let’s her sweat for a minute before she finally decides to put her out of her misery.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, calm down. I’m just playing with you. She didn’t even notice you weren’t here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda you play too much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why are you late anyway?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I cooked dinner last night, and my boy Trevor came by. We were just hanging out, drinking wine and talking. We lost track of time. I woke up on the sofa this morning and he was gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(devilish grin)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, I see...mm huh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t start that. He’s just a friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If you say so...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The phone rings. Wanda answers it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Attorney Spencers office, this is Wanda, how may I help you? Hold please. Speak of the devil...it’s your friend. You want to take the call here or in your office.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia places her hand out for the phone. Wanda hands it off to her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey home biscuit. I can’t believe you left me sleep on the sofa...oh is that right...I was looking too peaceful to wake up...thanks for cleaning up. You’re welcome. I had a good time too...later </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">gator</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda begins to sing to the beat of Biz Markie. Biz Markie cracks the office door open and sings along with Wanda. She doesn’t acknowledge his presence. He is a figment of her imagination. He disappears after Wanda finish singing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And she say he just a friend, and she say he just a friend...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Biz markie</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And she say he just a friend, and she say he just a friend...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia hangs up the phone and walks back towards her office smiling.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="9" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="11" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. miA APARTMENT-evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia enters her apartment. She takes a seat on the sofa and removes her shoes. She is massaging her tired feet. The door latch turns startling her. She hurries into the other room and returns with a baseball bat. She hides on the side of the door. The door slowly opens and Mia lunges out. A tall middle-aged man dressed in a pilots uniform enters the apartment. He jumps back to prevent from being struck by the baseball bat. He throws both his hands up in a surrender like gesture.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Antonio</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Mia...it’s</Text>
      <Text> me!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Antonio, I wasn’t expecting you back until tomorrow. You scared the crap out of me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry baby. They canceled by last flight due to weather, and I decided to surprise you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You almost got surprised.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both start laughing. He walks over and gives her a peck on the lips. She takes a seat on the sofa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How’s my baby doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She is rubbing her feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m good babe, my feet just aching.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sorry to hear that babe. I’m starving. Can you fix me something to eat?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia just shakes her head.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It would be nice if somebody would rub my feet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Your man hungry, fix me some food woman!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio gives her a kiss to indicate he’s joking. Mia rolls her eyes at him as he walks toward the bedroom. Mia enters the kitchen and prepares Antonio some food.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(o.s.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Babe, I’ll pay for you a massage. Anywhere you want to go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK. Thanks babe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="10" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="12" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia dining room-evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is setting a plate on the table for antonio. He enters and takes a seat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wow...greens, mac and cheese, when did you cook all of this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yesterday.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What was the special occasion?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No special occasion. I was talking to my boy Trev, and we both had a taste for some good food. We were tired of restaurant food, so I decided to cook!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio face is a little twisted up behind that comment, but he is trying to maintain his composure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh...Trevor was over here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="11" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="12" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>I/E. tREVOR APARTMENT-NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor is walking up to his door. He takes out his keys and unlocks the door. He enters to find a gorgeous woman in her mid 20’s who appears suddenly, starting him. She is wearing very little clothing. She has on a one-piece maid apron over a matching bra and panty set, and high heels. She has the figure to pull the look off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Autumn. What are you doing here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Surprise!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m definitely surprised. How did you get in?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I used the hidden key, don’t worry I was discreet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Umm...yeah, that wasn’t meant to be an open invitation to the crib Hun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry. I can leave. I just wanted to surprise you with dinner and show you how much I love you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t leave. Come here, it’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She walks over to him and hugs him trying to play innocent. He hugs her back and the give a little peck on the lips. He just shakes his head and smiles.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="12" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="13" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. trevor kitchen - evENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Honey, come on before the food gets cold.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor takes a seat at the table. Autumn places the plate of food in front of him. He looks scared to death to eat it. He takes a bite of the food and his face twists up indicating the food is not very pleasant. He secretly turns his head while she is not looking and spits the food into his napkin.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you like it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah...uhm...it’s good. I’m not that hungry. I had a big lunch today.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You don’t really like it do you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby, I appreciate your effort. Thank you, but I’m not with you for your cooking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor rises from the table and walks over to her taking her into his arms. His cell phone rings. He breaks away to answer the phone. Autumn pulls his arm in an attempt to keep him from answering the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t answer. You can call them back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, let me brag it real quick, it might be important. Hello...hey girl what up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor exits the kitchen and takes a seat on the sofa and forgets all about Autumn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn takes a deep breath and she looks pissed off.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="13" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="14" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. trevor living room-evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INTERCUT BETWEEN MIA AND TREVOR APARTMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="14" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="14" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia APARTMENT-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I didn’t catch you at a bad time, did I?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. I’m just chilling. What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I had to call and tell you the good news. We won that big trial I have been working on forever! I’m so happy it’s finally over.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Congratulations girl!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Trev</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have some good news to share with you too.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My script has been optioned!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia jumps up and down. She is very excited. Antonio is looking at her. He is frowned up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh my God. We have to celebrate!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m waiting for you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn is in the background listening to the conversation. She is frowned up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you coming to bed?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor speak in unison.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I gotta go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I gotta go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="15" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3/8" Page="15" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>Int. trevOR LIVING ROOM-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who was that, your friend Mia? I don’t get it what’s so special about her? Why do you need her as a friend? You have me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t trip. You don’t need to be jealous.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He pulls her toward him and they walk toward the bedroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="16" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="15" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. miA APARTMENT-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Celebrate what?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh I forgot to tell you, we won the big trial!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You called and told Trevor before you told me? How come you didn’t come and tell me first?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry baby, I thought you were asleep. I didn’t want to wake you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She seductively walks toward him giving him little kisses and they walk toward the bedroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="17" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 1/8" Page="16" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. lAW OFFICE-MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is walking toward the front office with a file in hand and Wanda is seated at her desk when a distinguished looking man in his </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">40’s</Text>
      <Text>  wearing a business suit enters the office.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The ladies are fidgety. Both of them are trying to help the man. They are speaking over each other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello. Who are you here to see?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ray</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Attorney Spencer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WaNDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who shall we say is here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The man flashes a smile.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Raymond Parker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Please have a seat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Wanda</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You can have a seat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda picks up the phone and dials.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Parker is here for his appointment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda hangs up the phone and Mia walks in the direction of Mr. Parker. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda, I will show him back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. I can show him back.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda hurries from behind her desk, but before she can get around the desk, Ray is already following behind Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mr. Parker, you can follow me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda puts her hands on her hips and rolls her eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You lead and I will follow. As you know my name is Raymond, but you can call me Ray. What’s your name? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m Mia and you can call me Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He laughs. Wanda stands watching with her hands on her hips looking disturbed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I like that a woman with a sense of humor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia returns to Wanda’s desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are we flirting with the clients?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Absolutely not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda imitates Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m Mia and you can call me Mia. What was that? Let us single women have a chance.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I am not interested in that man Wanda. Maybe some of you single ladies need to learn how to assimilate a little better.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s that suppose to mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing. I’m meeting up with Trevor to watch the game later. Want to hang?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No thank you. I hate watching boring sports. Grown men tossing balls around.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He is bringing one of his boys.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh in that case, I can learn to like sports. It’s all about assimilating, right?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She laughs mischievously.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="18" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="8 1/8" Page="18" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="BIZ MARKIE"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAYNE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. sports bar-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and wanda enter the sports bar. They approach a table where Trevor and his friend Dwayne are already seated. Dwayne is an average looking guy in his </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">30’s</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Wanda. You’re looking good girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is my boy Dwayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi Dwayne, it’s nice to meet you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Wayne</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The pleasure is all mine. Please call me Wayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Wayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What up Mia, Mia? Long time no see.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know, right.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>First round on me. What are you guys drinking?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll have a margarita.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Beer for me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Come on Mia, you can help me carry the drinks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor walk towards the bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m so hyped about your script!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks. It is surreal. How are you coming with your novel?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia shrugs her shoulders.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor are at the bar. Trevor places his drink orders. While they wait for the drinks, Mia shares pictures in her phone with him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here are some pictures from Anna and Mitch’s wedding.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia hands Trevor her phone. He is scrolling through the pictures and comes across some sexy pictures of Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah damn Mia, look at you. Sexy pictures.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boy give me my phone. Don’t look at those pictures.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia tries to take the phone from Trevor, but he pulls away. They are wrestling and tugging over the phone giggly like two little kids.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Cut TO table:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda and Wayne are watching Mia and Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up with those two?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>They say they’re just friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Biz Markie pops up in between Wanda and Wayne. He is a figment of Wanda’s imagination. He sings a line from his song.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>BIZ MARKIE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And she say he just a </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">friend...she</Text>
      <Text> say he just a friend...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>No one in the scene acknowledges Biz presence, as he is a figment of Wanda’s imagination. They continue with their conversation; when he finishes, he pops right back out of the scene.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You see it to, don’t you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah I do.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Everybody knows men and women can’t be just friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes they can.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No they can’t. You keep telling yourself that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have female friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, but have you ever stopped to think that the friendships are probably default friendships?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What is a default friendship?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>In some cases one friend is unattractive and attracted to the other, and they play the that’s my sister or that’s my brother role, better yet both friends are attracted to each other, but at least one or both are attached in a relationship; like Mia and Trevor who started out attracted to each other but neither of them has ever been single at the same time, so they just defaulted to friendship. Whatever the case, neither wants to lose the other from their lives.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia returns to the table with a margarita and beer interrupting the conversation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you two talking about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda was schooling me on the fact that men and women can’t be just friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh no, not the Wanda male and female friend theory.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WanDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know I’m right. If I were to take a poll in here right now, every male and female so called friendship is by default. You let one of them slip up tonight and drink too much, that friend that is secretly waiting for the right opportunity is going to make their move. It’s like playing with fire baby!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor gets stopped by a group of girls on his way back to the table. Mia is distracted from Wanda conversation, as she is eyeballing Trevor with the girls.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Look at her watching him. She is jealous.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wayne laughs.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I heard that. I am not jealous.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh, I have more. I’m going to write a book like Steve Harvey did.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor returns to the table. He hands Wayne his beer.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Game time folks! Who you pulling for Wanda?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I like that team with those cute little light skin boys...the swish brothers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She is talking about Golden State.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you for that Mia. I like that Chef Curry, he be cooking them up!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor gives Wanda a high five. She looks under eyed at Mia and grins.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah...Wanda talking shop!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda you’re a sports fan, I see.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, I love sports. I was just telling Mia earlier, how much I love sports. Who you pulling for Wayne?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia shakes her head.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Golden State baby! Got’s to go with the splash brothers!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, Bron is a beast. I’m sticking with Cleveland.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAyNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bron is a crybaby. Who you pulling for Mia?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t care who wins. I like both teams.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No Mia, you have to pick a team. No straddling the fence.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. If I have to pick, then I’ll have to go with the CAVs. I like Bron </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Bron</Text>
      <Text>.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How cute they picked the same team.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The game has started. Everyone is focused on the screen. Screaming out random calls, as if the players can actually hear them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get the ball.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Shoot!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why is he passing? Shoot the ball!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda is looking around at everybody yelling. So she decides to chime in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good interception!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Everybody looks at her. She smiles, clueless that she just used football lingo for basketball.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, that was a real nice steal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, that’s what I meant.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wayne looks at Wanda and smiles and winks at her. He likes her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It’s half time. Wanda spots Raymond, the guy from the law office, sitting at the bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia, isn’t that the guy from the office?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, it is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s go and speak.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know if...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Before Mia can finish speaking Wanda sashays toward Ray, who is seated at the bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Funny meeting you here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia exits her seat and walks toward the bar where Ray is sitting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry, have we met?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks up and stands next to Wanda. Ray instantly recognizes Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia is it, from Attorney Spencer’s office?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That is correct. Hello Mr. Parker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Please call me Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda clears her throat, making her presence known.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello, I am still standing here, rude people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Please forgive me beautiful. What was your  name again?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WanDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you watching the game alone?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray can’t take his eyes off of Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. I am watching...the game...alone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>Cut TO TABLE:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, I’m feeling old girl Wanda.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah Bro. </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">she</Text>
      <Text> is good people.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t really tell if she’s interested or not.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, all you have to do is show a genuine interest in what interest her. Women are emotional and sensitive creatures who want attention and conversation. Throw in a glass of wine and you are sure to hit a home run.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">CUT TO BAR:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda is looking frustrated with being ignored.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WanDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m going back over to the table to talk to Dwayne. Are you coming?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. I’ll be right there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda walks off. She takes a seat next to Dwayne. Trevor leaves the table and ventures towards the group of girls he was talking to earlier.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Wanda, I would love to hear more about your man and woman friendship theories. I find the topic to be very interesting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda perks up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You would?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Absolutely.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wands is rummaging through her purse as she continues talking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s face it; men and women have very little in common. If it weren’t for sex and reproduction men and women would have no reason to be together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s debatable. We’re all hanging out tonight.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda looks under the table. She continues to share her theory.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah I know. I’m sorry, I can’t find my phone. I need to run out to the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll go with you. I want to hear more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda and Wayne get up from the table, and walk towards the exit. She continues sharing her theory as they walk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You and Trevor don’t have the same type of friendship that Mia and Trevor have. It can never be the same. They are attracted to each other, whether they want to admit it or not. They will find any excuse to be around each other. Mia doesn’t care about this game. Thing about it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You make a good point.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="19" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="26" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAYNE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. sportS BAR-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay, I’ll take it one step further (phone rings). Oh wait that’s my phone. Hello, hey Mia. No, I’m not </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">upset...I’m</Text>
      <Text> not leaving. I couldn’t find my phone. I thought I left it in the car. We’re on our way back in.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Finish your thought.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>As for me, if I were in a relationship, there is no way my man could have a female best friend who he hangs out with on the regular. That shit would have to end. It’s just a matter of time before the sex kicks in and then comes the relationship, and I’m out in the cold. Antonio is crazy for letting Mia hang out with Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Interesting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda and Wayne are walking back inside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girls want love, boys want sex, girls want to cuddle, boys want to be left alone, girls want dinner dates, boys want sports dates, girls want stimulating conversation, boys want to be stimulated, girls want a beautiful lovemaking session, boys want to come. Need I go on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have a put a lot of thought into this. I’d love to debate this topic over dinner and a glass of wine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda softens up and blushes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh really. I would like that Dwayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="20" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="27" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. spoRTS BAR-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda, Dwayne and Trevor return to the table at the same time. Trevor winks at Dwayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Transition">
      <Text>CuT TO BAR:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Ray are still talking.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why don’t you join us?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RaY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I wouldn’t want to impose upon your dates.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh no, they’re not dates. Come on, the game is about to start back up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Ray walk toward the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey guys, this is Ray. He is going to join us for the second half of the game. Ray, this is my friend Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Todd, it’s good to meet you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s Trevor, Bro.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My apologies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And this is Dwayne.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The guys fist bump. Trevor energy shifts. He appears uncomfortable now that Ray has joined the group.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia your drink is almost empty. Would you line another?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure. Thanks Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray exits the table, and turns back before walking away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Would anybody else like a drink?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll take a margarita.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The guys nod no.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia I would have got you another drink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Trev</Text>
      <Text> it’s cool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="21" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 3/8" Page="29" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia APARTMENT-night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio is sitting on the sofa with the lights dim. Mia enters the house.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey babe. What are you still doing awake?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where have you been?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Watching the game with Wanda and Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up with this dude? What man wants to hang out with women? Is he gay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. He’s not gay. What’s wrong with hanging out with women?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not hanging out with a woman unless sex is involved. I’d rather watch the game with my boys.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah if you had any.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ha-ha.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You and I hang out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yep, and sex is involved.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You never had any female friends?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Before or after the sex?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’re friends, aren’t we?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’re not friends. You’re my woman.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh really, so we’re not friends?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Now Mia is pissed and he knows it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean yeah we’re </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">friends...uh...you</Text>
      <Text> know what I mean baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m so sick of you and your chauvinistic views.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not a chauvinist. I would vote for Michelle Obama, if she ran for president.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks out of the room and leaves Antonio standing alone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="22" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 2/8" Page="30" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mIA APARTMENT-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Scene opens with Mia doing a photo shoot of Trevor. He is posing for the camera.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tilt your chin down a little. Perfect, hold that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia clicks away, taking a few more photos of Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. I think we’re good. You should have enough to choose from for your promo material.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What can’t you do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I thought you knew. My nickname is superwoman.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks for doing this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Anything for you boo. Did you still need me to look over that option agreement?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Would you? That would be great!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor pulls the agreement out of his bag and hands it to Mia. She takes a seat and puts on her reading glasses to look over the agreement. Trevor looks at her admiringly. He picks up the camera and begins snapping photos of her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you doing? I look a mess.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You look beautiful. I think you are the most beautiful in your natural state.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you, but could you please stop?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So far everything looks to be in order here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When are you going to let me read your novel?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s not ready yet, and you know how I am?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes a perfectionist.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just like to have things right. I tell you what, how about I read you an excerpt?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Great idea! I’ll get changed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia prepares her and Trevor a glass of wine. She takes out her computer and searches for an excerpt to read to Trevor. He returns in his casual clothes and stretches out on the floor. Mia begins to read.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Abigail fully realizes her career has caused her to be a bit cynical when it comes to so-called love, as she counsels so many women and men alike who have suffered from tremendous heartbreak. She has cried tears of pain with her clients, and just from the empathy alone it’s more than she is willing to adhere to. She realizes that </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">being</Text>
      <Text> a therapist does not make her immune to the pitfalls of emotions that come with sharing your heart with someone, and she is terrified of losing control and letting go, for the pain would be far too much for her to bear. Abby always align herself with men similar to her, men who are emotionally unavailable, and this is why internet dating has become her safe haven. She turns to one of her favorite online dating sites merely to amuse herself. She is in her safe zone and is more than turned on by the power she possesses behind the screen and her ability to get these physical creatures aroused merely by her words. Could this prove men are just as cerebral as women and want their minds stimulated as well? Have men been dealt an unfair hand? She ponders before typing her next sentence. Of course, her psychologist mind can’t help but to analyze the men. It’s all part of the intrigue.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That was amazing. I want to hear more!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks. Glad you liked it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You are the perfect woman. Antonio is one lucky man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not quite. Sometimes I drink too  much, I’m never satisfied and I don’t like people very much.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both laugh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you like me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia looks at him lovingly.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I do like you Mr. Wright.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There is a moment between them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio walks through the door. He gives Trevor a cold stare before barely opening his mouth to speak.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey babe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>(Grunts)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He walks straight to the bedroom.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m going to go. Thanks for everything.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor collects his belongings and kisses Mia on the cheek before exiting.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="23" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 5/8" Page="33" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia aPARTMENT-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio is reading the newspaper when his cell phone rings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Ma, you got my message?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ma (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah baby. What’s going on? Sounded important.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve been doing a lot of thinking about my future and I am going to ask Mia to marry me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Marriage is a big commitment, are you sure about this son?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sure. I just wanted your blessing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re not still troubled by that man friend of hers are you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nope. All that’s going to change once she’s my wife. He will be out of the picture.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t fool yourself baby. Life doesn’t miraculously change just because you say I do. Why am I getting the feeling this proposal has a little more to do with this friend than your saying?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just don’t trust him. I’m going to put a stop to that friendship. You’re the one who told me men and women can’t be friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know. But I also told you; you can’t control another person’s emotions or decisions. You better be careful with this. It could backfire on you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re right Ma. It sounds like Mia is on her way in. I’ll talk to you later.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay baby. I love you. Good luck.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia enters the apartment carrying grocery bags. Antonio goes to help her with the bags.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey sweetie. I’m sorry about the way I’ve been behaving lately. How was your day.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I had a good day.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have bee thinking a lot about our future together. What do you really want from this relationship?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m good with the way things are.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I can be honest, I can’t help but to get a little jealous of the friendship you have with Trevor. I want that with you, and I really feel left out sometimes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Making you feel left out is the last thing in this world I ever want to do. Trevor is my friend, you are the man I love.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I love you too Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio drops down on one knee and pulls a box out of his pocket. Mia is in shock.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia, will you marry me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes! The answer is yes!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio places the ring on her finger. They embrace and kiss.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh my God. I can’t believe this is happening.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio hands Mia the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why don’t you call Trevor and share the good news with him. I know how you like sharing things with your buddy. I’ll unpack the groceries.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah...uhmm...okay, I guess I can give him a call now. (</Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Sarcastic</Text>
      <Text>) thanks for your thoughtfulness.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio flashes a sinister smile. She dials the phone. Antonio can be seen in the distance eaves dropping on her call with a huge grin on his face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Trevor. How are you doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="24" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="36" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. trevor APARTMENT-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INTERCUT BETWEEN MIA AND TREVOR APARTMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up girl? Are you okay? You sound like something is wrong.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, I’m good. It’s just been a crazy unpredictable day. You know how it is?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn enters the room while Trevor is on the phone. She rolls her eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell Mia I said hi.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Autumn say’s hello.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have something to tell you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What? Nothing bad, I hope.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, not unless you consider marriage bad. Antonio asked me to marry him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re getting married? Wow. Congratulations.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn jumps up in excitement practically break dancing. She is so happy with the news she just heard!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh my God, Mia is getting married, that is great news!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio is in the distance smiling.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(quietly)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="25" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="37" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mIA APARTMENT-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio walks in with a big smile on his face eating some popcorn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AnTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Did you reach Trevor?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah I did.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What did he say when you told him the good news?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(dryly)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Congratulations.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What was he suppose to say?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">OK</Text>
      <Text> then. Want some popcorn?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No thanks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What? You love popcorn. I never have known you to turn down popcorn. I put real butter on it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m tired. I’m going to take a nap. Enjoy your popcorn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He sits on the sofa smacking on his popcorn. He puts his legs up on the coffee table, wiggling his toes in shear delight. He grabs the remote and sits back to relax with a big accomplished smile on his face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="26" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5 2/8" Page="38" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. sPORTS BAR-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Wand enter the sports bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Work was crazy today. I really need a stiff drink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It wasn’t any different than any other day. You just seemed a little stressed today. You want to talk about it?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is it that obvious? I  hope I made the right decision to marry Antonio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s going on to make you question your decision?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have really been thinking if I love Tony enough to marry him. He’s a good catch; I don’t want to let him get away and some other woman reap the benefits.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re selling yourself short if you don’t love him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I do love him...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia cell phone rings. She answers it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hello. Hey Trev what’s up? I’m over here at </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Boca</Text>
      <Text> bar having a drink. Why don’t you swing by.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How did Trevor take the news about your getting married?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda you need to stop. How many times do I have to tell you? He is just a friend. He was happy for me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Biz Markie appears as a figment o Wanda’s imagination and sings along with her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She say he just a friend...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor enters the bar and takes a seat at the table with the ladies.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Wanda, how’s it going?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t complain. Aren’t you excited for our girl here getting married?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No doubt. As a matter of fact, let’s get a round so we can toast to the news.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray enters the bar and walks toward Mia’s table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are we toasting to?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia is getting married!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is that right Mia?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, I’m getting married.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Congratulations next round on me. May I join you guys?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure. You all are going to have me tipsy with all these drinks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s wrong with that? You’re a grown woman. I’m sure you can handle it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What brings you out tonight?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Truthfully...I</Text>
      <Text> was hoping to run into you. Although I’m a little thrown by this engagement business. I still have time to change your mind.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda begins fake coughing obnoxiously.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh excuse me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Bro. You’re coming on a little strong don’t you think? You’re bordering on disrespectful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Disrespectful to whom, she’s not your woman now is she?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No man, but this is my girl. We are sitting here celebrating her engagement and you’re disrespecting her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia, your boy here seems to think I’m disrespecting you, do you feel the same? I’m just keeping it real. You’re and attractive woman.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Everything is cool. Guys just chill out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Damn, I thought I was going to see a fight tonight!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ray</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, no fighting here baby. I’m a lover.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The bar maid brings over drinks. The music is playing. Mia and Ray are engaged in joyful conversation, they are both laughing. Trevor is looking disgusted and Wanda is looking irritated. She get’s up and walks away from the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s dance baby.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray takes her hand and leads her to the dance floor. Mia is tipsy; she and Ray are dancing freaky. Trevor is looking uncomfortable.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor walks towards the dance floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Excuse me a minute </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">bro.</Text>
      <Text>; I need to holler at my girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray throws up both of his hands in the air indicating it’s all good with him, he takes a step back. Ray signals for Wanda to come and dance with him. Wanda walks to the dance floor and dances with Ray. Mia and Trevor walk off the dance floor and sit at the table.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up with you? You’re out here freaking with this dude like you’re not about to be getting married.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m just having a little fun man, lighten up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m just trying to look out for you. You’re grown, have your fun, but watch yourself. Something doesn’t feel right about that brother.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thanks for looking out for your girl. Come on, you dance with me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor and Mia walk to the dance floor and begin to dance next to Wanda and Ray. Ray and Mia smile at each other both ignoring their dance partners. The song changes and Ray abruptly pulls Mia towards him away from Trevor. Trevor and Wanda are both pissed off. Wand and Trevor are left standing on the dance floor alone. They both yell at Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re just going to leave me standing here by myself?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Man, you’re disrespectful on so many levels. Hey Mia, I’m out of here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor walks off the dance floor and Mia goes after him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text AdornmentStyle="0" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why are you getting so upset? I don’t want you to leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TreVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If I stay around here, I might have to take that brother down. I’m tired anyway. I’ll holler at you tomorrow. Be careful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK. I’ll call you tomorrow.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda walks up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You should have Mike </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Tysoned</Text>
      <Text> his ass!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They all laugh. He gives the ladies a hug and exits. Mia walks over to the table where Ray is seated and pulls him to the dance floor. They embrace in a slow dance. The dance is getting a bit intimate. Wanda is staring at them and turning up her nose, she walks over to the dance floor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Excuse me, I hate to break up this little party, but it’s getting late.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ray</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let your girl finish the dance. She’s going to be an old married woman soon. I’ll buy you another drink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t need you to buy me anything. I’m about to go. Come on Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda just go on. I’ll be okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you sure? You had a lot to drink</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RaY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll make sure she get’s home safe.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s exactly what I’m afraid of. Call or text me when you get home. Don’t forget.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I will. Good night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl you better watch out for that snake.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda makes a hissing noise like a snake and strikes her hand out like a snake toward him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why I got to be all that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="27" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="43" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. sportS BAR-night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray walks Mia to her car. They are both a little tipsy it’s apparent by they’re staggered walk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Well, good night Ray. Thanks for walking me to my car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She reaches out to shake his hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No problem. Can I at least have a hug?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They hug, lingering a bit too long for Mia’s comfort. She pulls away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good night.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray opens the car door for her and he walks away. Ray turns around toward Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">wait...I</Text>
      <Text> almost forgot.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He walks toward the car. Mia steps out of the car.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What did you forget?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He immediately grabs her and starts kissing her, she pushes him away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You shouldn’t have done that. I’m getting married.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry. You’re right, please forgive me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="28" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. law office parking lot-mia car-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia pulls into the office parking lot. Her and Wanda exit the car carrying bags of fast food. They walk toward the office building.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What happened last night after I left?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing. We left shortly after you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is avoiding eye contact.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Why are you avoiding eye contact with me? Something happened. You better tell me now!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>All right, Ray kissed me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda stops in her tracks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What? I knew he was trouble!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I feel so bad.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I knew I shouldn’t have left you alone with that snake.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="29" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="5/8" Page="44" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. lAW OFFICE-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Wanda enter the office. Wanda takes a seat at her desk. Mia pulls up a chair to Wanda’s desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda, I’m scared. I don’t want to lose Antonio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>And you’re not going to. There is no need for him to ever know about this. Now, what are you going to do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Avoid Ray like the plague.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A man enters the office his face is concealed by a large bouquet of flowers. The bouquet is removed to reveal the face of Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Both ladies gasp. They look at each other and then back at Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The plague just entered the room</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="30" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 6/8" Page="45" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAYNE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. fishing bank-day</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor and Wayne are sitting on the fishing bank. Trevor tosses his line into the water while Wayne tries to bait the hook of his pole. Trevor sits back comfortably waiting for a fish to bite. He picks up a beer and takes a drink. Wayne is still fumbling around with the bait; he is squeamish about touching the worm. He is trying to bait the hook without touching the worm, but he eventually has to pick the worm up. When the slimy texture touches his hand he drops it. He is trying to pick the worm back up after a few attempts, Wayne finally gets his hook baited and tosses his line into the water.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wow man, you had a bit of a challenge there, I see.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No Bro. I was just </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">uh...yeah...you</Text>
      <Text> know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both start laughing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool. I don’t even bait with real worms anymore.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ah now you tell me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sorry, it was too much fun watching you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is my first time fishing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(sarcastically)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. Are you for real? I never would have guessed it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You got jokes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Both men laughing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How you feel about your girl getting married?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Funny you should ask. Ever since she told me about the engagement, I have been experiencing some mixed emotions.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What you mean?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know Mia is like a sister to me. She is genuinely my friend, but I’m having feelings for her bro, like I want to be with her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Parenthetical">
      <Text>(laughing)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You slow bro., I have been known that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How could I not see it all these years?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You didn’t want to. You were happy having Mia by your side. Through all your women, she has been your constant. Always there to cushion the blow following the big break ups. Let’s face it she has always been your </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">G-rated</Text>
      <Text> girl friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I never thought about it like that. That was kind of wise dude. Should I tell her how I feel?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You want to tell her now? Now that she’s getting married? That’s some selfish shit man even for you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know what to do. I need her. What should I do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just let her be happy. You’re not ready for a woman like Mia. What’s the longest you have been in a committed relationship, like 8 month’s?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s up with you and Wanda?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We’re supposed to hang out. I’m working on being a default friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>My man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The guys give each other a fist bump.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dwayne’s line starts jerking. He jumps up and attempts to reel in the catch. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I got me one!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He reels it in and takes it off the hook.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s a good catch!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah, but I’m going to throw it back in. It’s all fun and games for me!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Dwayne tosses the fish back into the water. Both men sit in silence for a moment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you going to do?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know yet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor get’s a bite. He reels it in and takes the fish off the hook and keeps it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="31" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="48" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. lAW OFFICE-MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray enters the office. He approaches Wanda’s desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good morning Ray. Do you have an appointment with attorney spencer today?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ray</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. I’m here to see Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay. I’ll call her and let her know your here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda picks up the phone and dials.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ray is here to see you. I’ll let him know. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda hangs up the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ray she’ll be right with you. Have a seat.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks to the front reception area toward Ray.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Good morning Ray. What are you doing here?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ve been calling you. Why haven’t you returned my calls?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Keep it down. You can’t just show up at my job like this. Let’s step outside.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda stands up and puts her hands on her hips. She stares Ray up and down.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m right here if you need me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="32" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="49" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. lAW OFFICE-MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Ray</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia it’s rude not to return a persons call. What did I do to you? I thought we were feeling each other.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ray I was going to call you because we do need to talk. You know my situation. You’re a cool guy, and if I were single things may have played out differently, but I’m going to have to ask you to stop calling me. Please don’t take it personal.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Just give me a chance to change your mind about getting married. Didn’t you feel something when we kissed?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I won’t deny there is an attraction. You have no idea how hard this is for  me. All we can ever be is friends; I’m going to marry Antonio.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Friends. I don’t play that little friend game that you and your boy got going. I know what I’m feeling for you, and it’s not friendship. Forgive me for coming to your job, but time is of the essence here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have to get back inside. If we can’t be friends there is nothing further for us to talk about. Please don’t call or come to my job again.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s really how you want it? Cool. I’ll see you around. Maybe sooner than you think. Sleep with one eye open you tease.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks back into the office. Wanda is standing by the door keeping a look out for her girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="33" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="50" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. lAW OFFICE-MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, it was looking real intense out there. What did you tell him?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I basically told him not to call or come here anymore.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you think he is going to honor that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I hope so. He threw out a little threat as he walked away.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I will cut that fool, with his fine ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you think I should tell Antonio?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hell to the </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">Naw</Text>
      <Text>! He will never understand. Men can’t imagine their woman in certain situations.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I feel like I owe it to him. Whey you marry someone you shouldn’t go into it with secrets.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, if it were me, I would take it to the grave. You’re crazy if you think he is going to understand or believe nothing happened but a kiss. Go ahead, be a fool and tell him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks back to her office. Wanda phone rings. She answers it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Attorney Spencer’s office, this is Wanda, how may I help you? Ray why are you calling here? She doesn’t want to talk to you anymore.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not calling for her. I actually called to talk to you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you want to talk to me about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="34" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="51" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>I/E. lAW OFFICE-MORNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>We see Ray leaned up against a building talking on his phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>The truth is, I have been feeling you every since we danced together, but I didn’t know how to come at you since your girl was showing so much interest. You already think I’m a snake with your mean self.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda softens she scrunches up her lips and takes a moment before responding.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you for real? I don’t really think you’re a snake. I know you’re a snake. You better stay away from girl and me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know you want me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Your ass is crazy for real.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tick tock, tick tock,, tell your girl to watch her back. Nobody plays Ray Parker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Ray lets out a wicked laugh and hangs up the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia returns to the reception area with a file in her hand. Wanda hangs up the phone. She is jittery.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia we got trouble.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia places the file on Wanda’s desk.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes we do. I just pulled Parkers file. He hired attorney Spencer to defend him on stalking charges.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda opens up the file and looks.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh damn. He just called here, and it wasn’t a friendly call. You better be careful. He is creepy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What did he say?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="35" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>I/E. mIA APARTMENT-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia rushes into her apartment and locks the door behind her. She leans up against the door after locking it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="36" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mIA APARTMENT-bathroom-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia turns on the shower. Her phone is ringing in the other room. She doesn’t here it. She prepares to get into the shower. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="37" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mIA APARTMENT-bedroom-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is out of the shower and putting on a pair of sweat pants and a </Text>
      <Text AdornmentStyle="-1" Background="#FFFFFFFFFFFF" Color="#000000000000" Font="Courier Final Draft" RevisionID="0" Size="12" Style="">T-shirt</Text>
      <Text>. She hears a noise. She picks up her house phone and dials.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Trevor. What are you doing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="38" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="52" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. tREVOR APARTMENT-evening</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Watching a movie with Autumn. Are you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>INTERCUT BETWEEN TREVOR AND MIA APARTMENT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m cool. I was just being a baby; I thought I heard some noises. Antonio is away on flights for a couple of days.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you want me to come by?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No, get back to your movie. I’ll be fine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="39" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MIA APARTMENT-KITCHEN-EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks into the kitchen she searches for a knife. She hears a knock at the door. She slowly walks toward the door with the knife in her hand and looks out the peephole. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="40" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="3 1/8" Page="53" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mIA APARTMENT-living room-night</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She puts the knife down and opens the door to let Wanda in. Wanda rushes into the apartment out of breath. She has a large bag that she plops down onto the table top. She opens the bag and begins pulling out all types of weapons. She has a bee bee gun, a hunting knife and some mace.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda what are you doing here? What is all of this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, I came to protect my friend from that fool. I know Antonio is out of town and I was worried about you. I called you a couple of times.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I was probably in the shower. Wanda I didn’t know you had a gun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Girl, that’s a bee bee gun. I’ll shoot that fool in the eye.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Honestly, I was scared. I’m glad you’re here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>There’s a knock at the door. Both ladies jump. Wanda grabs the bee bee gun. Mia gets the mace. They both walk slowly towards the door. Mia yanks the door open and Wanda points the gun.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Brace yourself fool.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Whoa...ladies it’s me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They all laugh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I told you, you didn’t have to come.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now you know better than that. You sounded really worried. What’s going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You were right about Ray. He is crazy and he might be stalking me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yep, I knew something was off about that brother.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You can’t be friends with everybody. Mia you need to get a restraining order.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I agree with Wanda on that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I agree with you guys.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Wanda, you can take off if you want to. I’m going to stay here with Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia is that okay with you? Cause you know I can stay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s fine. I appreciate you coming by to help protect me girl.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know I got your back. Ya’ll can hold on to the weapons.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s all right you can take them.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’ll just leave the mace!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda gathers all her weapons up and walks toward the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia gives her a hug and Wanda exits.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That girl is nuts!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell me about it. Thanks for coming. I know Autumn is pissed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>She’ll be all right. You ready for the big day? It’s right around the corner.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know it’s coming fast. You want to see my dress?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sure.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia exits the room and returns with a beautiful modern wedding dress on. Trevor stands up and takes notice.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wow...absolutely beautiful.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia turns and models the dress for him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You make a beautiful bride. Antonio is a lucky man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He looks at her deeply for a moment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me go and take this off before I ruin it. I’ll grab you a blanket. You can crash out on the sofa.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia exits and returns wearing her sweats, with a sheet and blanket, she tosses them to Trevor. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here you go bodyguard.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s super-friend to you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor ties the sheet around his neck and begins doing his superman routine. He runs over to Mia and picks her up and pretends to fly around the room. Mia is screaming and laughing at the same time.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Put me down fool before you drop me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m not going to drop you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor tumble to the floor. She falls on top of him. They’re both laughing. Trevor looks into Mia’s eyes and they can’t break apart. Their lips meet and the first kiss between the friends is exchanged. They remain on the floor. He holds her in his arms.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="41" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 6/8" Page="56" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WAYNE"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. park - daY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda and Wayne are sitting outside in a park. They are off in the distance away from all the people. The two are comfortably laid out on a blanket, sitting underneath a tree. They are talking and laughing, enjoying some wine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Typically there is one thing that separates men and women from being just friends.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WayNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s that?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sex. Because by definition friendship is typically exclusive of sex, that’s why I coined the term default friendships. Basically, for men and women who have slept together, and became friends afterwards etc.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re so cute.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you Wayne. You’re not so bad on the eyes either.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I love smart women. I can listen to your theories all day.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Really? You’re not tired of listening to me talk?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Not at all.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both laugh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Here’s the clincher, default friendships are great for the men and women involved in them, but hell on the girlfriend, boyfriend or spouse.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAyNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can see that. It’s like the default friendship is more than just a friendship, there’s a deeper connection that only a man and woman can share, because of the sexual attraction.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Exactly! You’re a good student.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just have one question for you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can I be your default friend?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both laugh.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>If we become default friends, just know there can be no other default friends in your life. I run a tight ship. Are you ready for a woman like me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WAYNE</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Sounds like a challenge to me, and I never shy away from a good challenge.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda begins rambling on about something.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I can’t believe you’re not challenging my theory; most people want to challenge me...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wayne leans over and kisses her right in the middle of her talking. That shuts her up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="42" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 1/8" Page="58" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. trevor APARTMENT-NIGHT</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor is lying on the sofa in the dark. He is looking up at the ceiling. He begins to click the lamp switch on and off. Autumn enters the room.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby, are you all right? Come to bed.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I just have a lot on my mind. I can’t sleep. I’ll be in there, go back to bed sweetie.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He picks up his cell phone and strolls to Mia’s number, but decides not to call. He puts the phone down and begins to click the light on and off again. He reaches for the phone. This time he dials.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia, I know it’s late, but I was hoping you answered. I really wanted to talk to you. I guess we’re just going to pretend like that kiss never happened. I’ll respect that, but I can’t stick around and watch you marry this guy. You take care of yourself. Good luck with your marriage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn is hiding around the corner eavesdropping on his phone call. She appears upset by what she heard. He hangs up the phone and Autumn storms in the room. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You kissed her? How could you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Were you spying on me?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t you dare try to turn this around on me. You lied to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sick of this.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess that explains why you couldn’t answer your phone. You were too busy kissing your BEST FRIEND!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn storms out of the room he just looks up at the ceiling. He wakes up on the sofa the next morning he gets up from the sofa and walks toward his bedroom. He gets his luggage from the closet and begins packing clothes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="43" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 2/8" Page="59" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. trevor bedroom - morNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What’s going on? Why are you packing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m leaving town for a while. I need to clear my head on some things.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I gave up my apartment to move in here with you, and now you’re just going to up and leave!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry; I just need to make this move. You can stay here as long as you want. Don’t worry about the rent. I left some money on the night stand to help with the bills until I return.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>When is that going to be? </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me guess. This is about your best friend Mia getting married. I knew it; you’re in love with her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He just looks at her without responding and continues to pack his bags.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You’re a sweet girl Autumn, and I care about you, but this is not what I want for my life. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you crazy? Do you think I’m just going to let you leave me like this?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He gathers his bags and walk toward the door. Autumn runs behind him she tries to block him from leaving by standing in front of the door. He puts his bags down, picks her up and moves her to the side.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor please don’t leave me. I love you baby. She is marrying someone else. I forgive you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This is not about you; it’s not about Mia. This is about me. Pull yourself together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He walks down the sidewalk and never looks back. Autumn is on her hands and knees crying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="44" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 6/8" Page="60" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="RAY"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. mia APARTMENT-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is joyfully walking up her sidewalk outside of her apartment. She has a new hairdo. She approaches the door to her apartment and fumbles for the keys. She unlocks the door and walks in to see her fiance seated at the dining room table, and there is another gentleman seated across from Antonio. All she can see is the back of his head. The man slowly turns to face Mia. He has a big smile on his face. Mia loses it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What the hell are you doing in my house? Whatever he told you is a lie Tony. I can explain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Explain what? He was responding to the ad we put in the paper. You remember, apartment for rent?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Obviously your fiance has me confused with someone else. I should go. I’ll be in touch with my decision. Good luck with your marriage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is breathing heavily, she is very upset. Ray walks over to shake Antonio’s hand.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hell no! This little game you’re playing is going to stop right here and right now. You’re not Glenn Close and I am definitely not Michael Douglas.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Mia what is going on?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>This man has been stalking me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is this true Ray?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>No. If you’re going to tell it, tell the whole truth Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What is he talking about?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Nothing happened.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We had a little fling man. I was supposed to be her one last hit before getting married.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You liar!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia lunges at him and Antonio grabs her back. Ray is smiling that slick smile. Mia pulls off her shoes and throws them at him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s time for you to leave.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RaY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Gladly. Mia wasn’t that the best kiss you ever had among other things?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is crying.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Get the hell out of my house. I’m about one second off from putting my foot up your ass!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio walks toward him. Ray runs out of the house, still talking shit.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>RAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s cool. She’s in love with that male friend of hers anyway. You might want to check into that bro., she’s playing you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What have you done? Start explaining now!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I did not have an affair with him. You have to believe me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Something happened, that man is not going to be carrying on like that for no reason.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It was just one kiss. I’m sorry baby, please forgive me. I wanted to tell you, but Wanda said...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Stop right there. I don’t want to hear nothing Wanda big mouth said. Can’t trust none of ya’ll. This marriage is off!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio grabs his jacket; he throws his house keys, and storms out the door. Mia is sitting on the sofa sobbing. She picks up the phone to call Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor, call me back, it’s very important.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She checks her voice messages and hears the message Trevor left her.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia, I was hoping you answered. I really wanted to talk to you. I guess we’re just going to pretend like that kiss never happened. I’ll respect that, but I can’t stick around and watch you marry this guy. You take care of yourself. Good luck with your marriage.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia gets her car keys and purse. She drives to Trevor’s apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="45" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1" Page="63" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="AUTUMN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. mia car - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia pulls up in front of Trevor apartment. She parks the car and frantically walks up to the door. Mia is ringing the doorbell and pounding on the door.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor are you in there? Open up it’s me, Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She continues knocking still no answer. She searches through her purse for a pen and paper. She writes a note and sticks it in the door. She turns to walk away and the door slowly opens. Mia turns to face a frightful looking Autumn.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Mia (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hi, you must be Autumn. I’m Mia.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AuTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know who you are.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is Trevor here? I tried calling him, but something must be wrong with his phone. It keeps going straight to voice mail.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn tears up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>He’s gone</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What do you mean he’s gone?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I mean he packed up his bags and left.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where did he go?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>AUTUMN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know. If I did I wouldn’t tell you! This is all your fault.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Autumn slams the door in her face.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="46" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="7/8" Page="64" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>InT. miA CAR - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda, Trevor is gone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Where did he go?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I don’t know. I just left his apartment and Autumn said he packed up and moved out, and she has no idea where he is.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh no.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You have to help me find him. I need to tell him that I’m not getting married.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You called off the wedding? What the hell!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Ray showed up at the apartment. I’ll tell you all about it, but first let’s find Trevor. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have some ideas. I’ll meet you at your apartment.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wow we proved to everyone that men and women can be just friends, but why do I feel so sad and empty?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Was it worth the price?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="47" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 5/8" Page="65" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>ExT. miA APARTMENT - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>She takes a seat on the sofa and dials out on her cell phone. There’s a knock at the door. Mia opens the door to Wanda. Wanda is on high energy. She enters the apartment with a stack of missing posters in her hand with Trevor picture.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey girl, I made up these missing posters. We can put these up and start asking around.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia burst out laughing.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda you can’t be serious?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I am. I’m going to help you find Trevor. I put a call out to Wayne. I left him a voice mail. Have you tried to call Trevor anymore?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, but it just keeps going  straight to voice mail.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Don’t worry. We’ll find him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda, seriously we cannot put up those missing posters.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I already put up a couple.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh Lawdy.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell me what happened. Why did you call off the wedding?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I didn’t call it off, Antonio did. Ray showed up and convinced him we were having an affair.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WaNDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You know what? These kinds of things don’t happen by accident. It wasn’t meant for you to marry Antonio. This is fate; you and Trevor are meant to be together.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Do you really believe in that stuff? I’m so confused. If fate is real, why are both of them gone?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You just have to trust and believe. You remember that Prince song we use to groove to; Thieves in the temple. Remember the part when he said; Love come quick, love come in a hurry there are thieves in the temple tonight. That’s what I believe is happening. Every time you and Trevor paths cross there is some love thief keeping you two apart? You better open your eyes Mia. I know you think I’m crazy, but pay attention.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A knock is heard at the door. Mia and Wanda look at each other. Mia opens the door and it’s Antonio. He is carrying one of the missing posters that Wanda made.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What the hell is this? It was posted on the tree.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thieves in the temple, let me go.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Wanda snatches the poster from Antonio hand, they glare at each other and she walks out.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Can we talk?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes. I’m surprised to see you here.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I want to apologize for the way I handled things.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Your reaction was understandable. Ray was very convincing. He had us all fooled.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think I was more upset by what he said about you and Trevor than I was about him. Mia I need to know something. Are you in love with Trevor?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>It takes her a moment before she answers.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Trevor is one of my dearest friends. I love him as a friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is his friendship more important to you than being my wife?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you asking me to choose?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m asking you to be my wife.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio takes Mia in his arms and they kiss.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>We still got time to make it to city hall.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let’s do it!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="48" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 5/8" Page="67" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="WANDA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. miA CAR - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio is driving. He and Mia just left city hall. Mia is wearing her wedding dress and Antonio has on his suit. Mia’s phone rings.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey wanda!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I talked to Wayne. He tracked Trevor down.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Is he okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, he’s fine. Trevor is in California.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Say what? He’s in California?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WanDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yep, Wayne said he is going to get him an agent or something like that.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio ear perks up. When he hears that part of the conversation. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>OK I feel better now. At least I know he is fine.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yep, I agree. What did Antonio say?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I have something to tell you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’s married now!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You went through with the marriage?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Congratulations, I guess.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda, I’ll call you back. I’m going to call Trevor.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>WANDA (V.O.)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Okay.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia begins to dial the phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Put the phone down. You will not be calling Trevor anymore. Do I make myself clear? That friendship has come to an end.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Whatever. You can’t tell me who I can and cannot be friends with.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Try me Mia. I’m not playing with you. I have put up with that charade of a friendship long enough. I’m your husband now, and you will respect me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia hangs up the phone, her mood is somewhat down. Neither her nor Antonio says another word they drive in silence.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="49" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1 4/8" Page="69" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CARRI"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. literary agent office - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor is casually dressed in jeans and a T-shirt/hoodie. He enters a reception area of an office, but no one is seated up front. He looks around and walks toward the back. He peeks his head into an office and notices an attractive businesswoman in her 40’s typing on a computer. She never looks up. She doesn’t notice Trevor standing and watching her. He lightly taps on the door. Her office door reads Literary Management resources, Carri Jones. She looks up at him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Carri</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How may I help you?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I wanted to talk to someone about representation. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CARRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I see, and you didn’t think to call first?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I’m sorry ma’am. I’m from Chicago.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CARRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh I see, so you guys don’t make appointments in Chicago?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes, we do. I’m sorry. I have a script that is being optioned and I was told I should get representation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CARRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>In that case, take a seat. Today is your lucky day. Let me see what you got.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor hands Carri a copy of the script. She thumbs through it.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CARRI (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Leave me a copy and I’ll look over it. I’ll have my assistant call you if we’re interested in representing you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Thank you, Ms. Jones!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>CARRI</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Please call me Carri. You lucked up today. Don’t make it a practice of popping up in folks office out here in California. Word travels fast.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes ma’am. I mean Carri. Thank you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor shakes Carri hand and exits the office. Carri looks at him with an admiring smile.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor dials his phone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hey Mia, call me as soon as you get this message. I’m in California! Hey, sorry about the way I left, but I just needed to clear my head. Things are going good out here so far. I miss you girl!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>THREE YEARS LATER</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="50" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2 3/8" Page="70" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANGRY WOMAN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="CHEATING MAN"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. sports BAR-DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A blonde whose identity is not yet revealed is seated at the bar with an average looking male. The two are having drinks. A man sits off in the distance watching the couple while he sips from a cocktail filled glass. The couple does not notice they are being watched. The man at the bar rises from his seat and takes the woman by the hand. He attempts to forcefully pull her from her seat but she resists. The mystery man in the distance notices her uneasiness. He stands and begins to walk towards the couple. Out of no ware an angry Latina woman barges into the lounge charging in the direction of the couple. The woman abruptly jumps in between the two of them, she pushes the man with force as she screams to the top of her lunges at him. The blonde slowly eases back out of the way. She is startled when she feels someone behind her touching her arm, she quickly turns to see who is behind her. The blonde is revealed to be Mia. She appears shocked to see the handsome mystery man Trevor standing behind her. No words are exchanged between the two old friends, they deeply gaze into each other eyes. The angry woman continues yelling and hitting her cheating husband. He runs out the bar and she chases behind him. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Angry woman</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You cheating bastard, I’m going to kill you!</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>Cheating Man</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Honey wait. I can explain. She was coming on to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANGRY WOMAN</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>You liar...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia and Trevor watch the action taking place. They are both laughing as they take a seat at the bar.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Are you okay?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yes I’m fine. Trevor Wright! Look who just pops up in my life out of the blue?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They embrace in a hug.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wishes do come true. Little Miss Mia! You have no idea how long I have been looking for you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me buy you a drink for rescuing me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Now you know how I am. I can’t allow you to buy me a drink. How about I buy you a drink?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Always the Mans-man.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That’s me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>How long have you been back?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>About a year now. So...what’s with the get up?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>It’s a long story.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Who was that dude? Are you creeping on old Antonio?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Hell no! That was just a job.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor chokes on his drink.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What the hell kind of job you doing Mia? Please tell me you’re not...</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MiA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Boy you got jokes; I’m not a hooker.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I know. I was just joking with you. What’s with the wig and the hoochie gear?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Let me explain.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia takes a business card from her purse and hands it to Trevor. He reads the information contained on the card out loud.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Exposed Detective Agency. You suspect them and we catch them. What the hell? You work for a detective agency that catches cheaters?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I guess you didn’t hear about my tumultuous break-up with Antonio. He was cheating on me within the firs 6 months. At least that’s when I found out. My marriage didn’t even last a year.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>FLASHBACK:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A MONTAGE OF EVENTS ARE HIGHLIGHTED TO SHOW ANTONIO’S INFIDELITY.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="51" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="2/8" Page="73" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. MIA APARTMENT- </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks into the bedroom and Antonio is texting. He quickly puts the phone away when she enters. She doesn’t say anything, but she looks at him with suspicion. He doesn’t say a word.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="52" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="73" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. miA APARTMENT - living room - DAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>A different day, Mia enters the living room and Antonio is on the phone talking really low. Mia is watching him and listening to his conversation.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>What are you wearing?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>He turns to see Mia’s piercing eyes looking straight through him.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO (CONT’D)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah man, what are you wearing to the gala?</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia rolls her eyes and walks out. He picks up the newspaper. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Antonio is in the shower. Mia peeks around the corner into the bathroom to make sure he is actually in the shower before snooping through his belongings. She first checks through his phone, and snaps a photo of a text in his phone with her phone. Then she looks through his pants pockets and takes out his wallet. She finds a receipt and takes a picture of it. She places the receipt back in his wallet.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="53" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="1/8" Page="74" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats/>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>EXT. mia car - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia is in her car she trails behind Antonio as he pulls into the parking lot of a park. He exits his car. Mia stays in the distance watching him from her car as he exits his car. A woman approaches him they embrace in a hug.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="54" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="4/8" Page="74" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="ANTONIO"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>ExT. park - dAY</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia exits out of her car and tip toes, hiding behind bushes and trees. Pink Panther style music is playing in her head, as she tips toes closer. She snaps a picture of Antonio kissing the woman. Steam is coming from her ears, she is so angry. She tries to maintain her composure, but she loses it, and runs towards Antonio in full attack mode. She pushes him in the chest.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>The other woman stands off to the side. She looks for a brief moment before quietly slipping away without a word.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Wanda was right about you.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>ANTONIO</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Baby wait, I can explain. She’s just a friend.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Mia walks away leaving Antonio standing alone.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>END FLASHBACK:</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Number="55" Type="Scene Heading">
      <SceneProperties Length="6/8" Page="74" Title="">
        <SceneArcBeats>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="MIA"></CharacterArcBeat>
          <CharacterArcBeat Name="TREVOR"></CharacterArcBeat>
        </SceneArcBeats>
      </SceneProperties>
      <Text>INT. BAR - EVENING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Oh wow, that’s messed up.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Tell me about it. I started the company after turning into Mrs. Sleuth to catch his cheating ass.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>That dude use to hate me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think your girl hated me more.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>They both laugh. They are exiting the bar and still conversing. </Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>Yeah. You have a point there.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>MIA</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>I think Antonio was more obsessed with keeping us apart than he was with being married to me.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text>TREVOR</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text>So, you’re divorced now? (Sly smile)</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>Trevor takes her hand and looks into her eyes.</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text>THE END or THE BEGINNING</Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Dialogue">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Action">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Type="Character">
      <Text></Text>
    </Paragraph>
  </Content>

